Gabe K wrote a review Dec 2023
3 contributions1 helpful vote
Great massage!
This was a very lovely massage! I got the Thai massage with Qua. Qua did a fantastic job and was extremely nice. I highly recommend booking here! The hospitality was excellent in a very relaxing environment with kind people.
Lennu wrote a review Dec 2023
Jyväskylä, Finland22 contributions4 helpful votes
Amazing 3 nights in most beautiful boutique hotel
Just amazing small boutique hotel. Most beautiful design, very helpful staff, great breakfast, comfortable beds, clean rooms. And a nice Koi pond in the middle of the lounge! Try their omelette, was the best one yet in Vietnam. Stayed here for 3 nights on a north-to-south tour of whole Vietnam.
Shu Wen wrote a review Nov 2023
Singapore, Singapore1 contribution
Felt like home!
This place felt like home to me. It was my first time travelling to Vietnam hence having the receptionists take care of me as a solo female traveller was very heartwarming. Phoebe was assigned to me as a local friend who communicated to me via Whatsapp on my needs (such as car booking/ food recommendations/ room service/ massage suggestions). I literally just explored Da Nang and Hoi An without an itinerary and when I am hungry or feel like checking out a different place, Phoebe would share her recommendations for my consideration. If you are a solo traveller, I recommend you just rest your mind and let them suggest how you should explore the city. Room was cozy and clean, something I was very particular about. Breakfast selection was minimal but local food was tasty (they…
Date of stay: October 2023
Vic wrote a review Nov 2023
Torrejon De Ardoz, Spain10 contributions
Modern hotel with pool with amazing staff, close to the beach, and tasty breakfast
The people working at the hotel were very nice, helpful and attentive. The rooms were clean, comfy, and with a modern touch. Breakfast was delicious, and with different options. The hotel has a rooftop pool, and a beautiful interior pond with fish. The beach is only 5 minutes from the hotel. 100 % recommended if you're spending a few days in Da Nang. :)
Date of stay: November 2023
Iman L wrote a review Nov 2023
6 contributions
Excellent stay
The hotel made our trip in Vietnam. The customer service is excellent and the architecture of the hotel is so relaxing and zen. We definitely loved it! The location is great yo get quick acces to the beach and the ancient town of Da Nang!
Carla E wrote a review Oct 2023
4 contributions1 helpful vote
Okish hotel, nice staff
Nice small hotel, close to city center. Very friendly and caring staff. Bedsheets were little dirty and also the room (especially the floors) were not very clean (dead worm in bathroom and kitchen sink) and dirty cups. Pool only has two daybeds, no other chairs. Also only accessible via stairs. So not suitable for handicapped people. Staff was very very nice. I stayed for one night. That was ok, but wouldn’t stay longer. Also due to night club next door it is quite noisy.
Lizbeth W wrote a review Sep 2023
Los Angeles, California10 contributions
Serene oasis and near the beach
Beautiful wooden architectural details from the outside entrance to the reception area are the first thing we noticed. We were warmly welcomed with cold tea and coconut biscuits by the serene koi pond. Our garden view rooms were very comfortable and thoughtfully laid out. We liked the clean modern aesthetic in the wooden chairs and handles in the bathroom area. The sink was a beautiful granite bowl. Enjoyed the piped in music and bird sounds. You control the volume or can turn it off if you don’t want to listen to it. Looking down into the interior garden from our 5th floor rooms was special. We enjoyed swimming in the lovely rooftop infinity pool each day. Breakfast was delicious with many choices of Vietnamese food. Western egg choices and toast were also available. Also…
Date of stay: September 2023
Jenny B wrote a review Aug 2023
Aberdeen, United Kingdom9 contributions7 helpful votes
A decent stay
Overall this was a good hotel ill broken down the good and bad bits below: Good: You get someone looking after you throughout your stay. They give you a WhatsApp no and you can message for things you need etc. This is a brilliant idea! Phoebe is amazing, she looked after us. She went above and beyond. Whatever you are paying her, she needs a raise. The staff were very helpful and cheery! It is down a side street so pretty quiet Pool was lovely Decoration is really nice and bed was comfortable Bad: I think the hotel recycles water which is great but this means that was this constant pump sound outside are room. Throughout our stay it was driving us mad and interfered with us sleeping. The breakfast was more Asian based which is expected as we are in asia but we skipped it most…
